    "history": {
        "short_description": "A 15th-century Jain temple built by Jain merchants, known for its unique Kerala-Jain architectural style.",
        "detailed": "The Jain Temple at Jainmedu is one of the rare surviving Jain heritage structures in Kerala. Built around the 15th century by a Jain merchant family, it once served as a center for a thriving Jain community in Palakkad. Constructed with granite and laterite, the temple features a long, narrow structure typical of Kerala’s traditional style. The shrine is dedicated to Chandraprabha, the eighth Tirthankara."
    },
